        <briefdescription>
<para>Check if a virtual address is within range of virtual memory. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This checks if the virtual address (<computeroutput>virt</computeroutput>) is within permissible range, e.g. between :kconfig:option:<computeroutput>CONFIG_KERNEL_VM_BASE</computeroutput> and (:kconfig:option:<computeroutput>CONFIG_KERNEL_VM_BASE</computeroutput> + :kconfig:option:<computeroutput>CONFIG_KERNEL_VM_SIZE</computeroutput>).</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>Only used if :kconfig:option:<computeroutput>CONFIG_KERNEL_VM_USE_CUSTOM_MEM_RANGE_CHECK</computeroutput> is enabled.</para>
</simplesect>
<parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>virt</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Virtual address to be checked.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>True if virtual address is within range, false if not. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
